@cailloup : One thing I've noticed about Windows 8 (at least with 64-bit edition since that is what i use) is that it doesn't like accepting files which are altered other than through an actual installation. This is a sort of security procedure i presume and is probably beneficial if we all live in an ideal world of buying genuine software which is cheap and affordable. And thus doesn't need to be run with patched files and pirated data. As that is not the case with our world anyway, here's the solution:

Install the game (and any other similar games you may have in the future) to another partiiton other than the primary one on which Windows-8 OS is installed. I have a "GAMES" folder in my "D" drive for all these "patched-and-pasted-over" things, while my entire C drive is used for Windows-8. This allows me to have all same game files intact.

Not just with this game, but so many others as well.
